snippet: Sergio García, once Tiger Woods’s projected foil, was eight over par on the back nine and finished at 75 in the first round of the W.G.C.-Cadillac Championship.
abstract: Adam Scott and Jason Dufner share first-round lead at WGC-Cadillac Championship golf tournament; Sergio Garcia shoots a brilliant five under par on the first nine, but collapses on the back nine to end up nine strokes back, a round that is somewhat reflective of Garcia's entire career.
lead_paragraph: Sergio García, once Tiger Woods’s projected foil, was eight over par on the back nine and finished at 75 in the first round of the W.G.C.-Cadillac Championship.

headline.seo: García Struggles in First Round of W.G.C.-Cadillac Championship
headline.main: At Doral, a Career Reflected in a Round
headline.print_headline: At Doral, a Career Reflected in a Round
